thai: náawng plaawy yen níi lǎng lôoek ngaan wâang mǎi já.
english: Ploy, are you free this evening after work?

thai: wâang khâ. mii à-rai hâi chûuai khá.
english: I'm free. Is there something you need help with?

thai: phîi gam-lang khít-khít yùu wâa yàak jà buu-chaa măa nâ jâ. phráw hěn wâa thuua rao gam-lang bpai dâai dii. gâaw looei yàak jà chuuan náawng plaawy bpai súue khǎawng wâai dûuai gan nâ khâ.
english: I am thinking that I want to worship the dog because I saw that our tours are going well. So then I wanted to ask you to go shopping to offer together.

thai: ǎaw...dâai sì khâ. ngán phlaawy jà rîip sà-sǎang ngaan hâi sèt gàawn wee-laa áawp-fít bpìt looei khâ.
english: Ah...I can do that. Well then, I'll hurry to clear up my work before the office closing time.

thai: mûuea-waan khun-phâaw hâi ngoen. chǎn gâaw looei bpai súue khà-nǒm gin.
english: Father gave me money yesterday. So I went to buy snacks to eat.
to worship, to honor, to pay respect
ahead of schedule ; ahead of time
